##Small and medium-sized enterprises cash flow emergency, lay-off staff waiting for support

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

The spread of the disease has made life even more difficult for small and medium-sized enterprises, which are already in the midst of an economic downturn. Although relief measures have begun to be introduced, they are looking for more extensive policy support, such as fee cuts and tax cuts

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure / IC

By Zhang Wei, CAIJING correspondent

Editor | Yuen Man

"after sitting for a day, the birds flew past 10 birds, 8 pedestrians and 30 vehicles. No suspicious circumstances were found. " Wu looked around through the floor-to-ceiling windows of the guesthouse. Affected by the outbreak of COVID-19 pneumonia ("new type pneumonia") , she has checked into only one of the five lodgings she has operated in Chongqing since January 20 and has stayed there for only two days.

If this continues until the end of March, wu Yu nearly two years of investment will be wasted: The early decoration costs, daily housing maintenance fees, the rent paid, the promotion platform access fees... the original plan during this year's Spring Festival to try to "get off to a good start, " Did Not want to eventually become her a person's loneliness and helplessness.

This feeling, far away from the Lin Ke is not unfamiliar. Lin Ke, head of a small travel agency in Beijing, was ordered to stop tour groups across the country as the outbreak worsened. He now has only one job: to help users quit the group.

"Even if the epidemic ends now, it will take at least half a year for the tourism industry to recover. Considering the later labor costs and so on, they may choose to disband the small team and find another sideline job. " Lin Ke typed several "depressed" in the wechat dialogue, finally, to "CAIJING" reporter said, "really not, go home to plant vegetables and raise pigs. ".

The impact of the new pneumonia epidemic is by no means limited to accommodation, tourism and other industries. In an article entitled "analysis of the impact of the epidemic on the Chinese economy and Policy Recommendations" (hereinafter referred to as "recommendations") , Ren Zeping, president of the Research Institute of Evergrande, pointed out that from the impact of the meso-sector, catering, tourism, film, transportation, education and training and other industries hit the hardest, medicine, online games and other industries benefit. A simple estimate: $7 BILLION IN BOX office sales (market forecasts) + $500 billion in retail sales (assuming a 50% cut) + $500 billion in tourism (a complete freeze) . In just seven days, the direct economic losses in these three sectors alone exceeded $1 trillion, accounting for 4.6% of GDP of $21.8 trillion in the first quarter of 2019, and that's not including other industries.

"under the nest, how to complete the egg. ". Epidemic Haze, in the industry of micro-individuals (small and medium-sized micro enterprises, individual operators, etc.) , has smelled the danger of the "smell. ".

Cash flow is tight

Under the epidemic, the first to be affected is the restaurant business operators. In order to prevent the spread of the epidemic, a number of catering enterprises were forced to suspend business, followed by rent, food backlog, personnel costs and other issues, all overnight in front of them.

"This is not an impact or a shock for the catering enterprises, but a blow, " Jia Guolong, chairman of Xibei Naked Face Village (hereinafter referred to as "Xibei") , told Caijing that Xibei wanted to "make a big impact" in 2020, to reverse a less favourable development in 2019, but the sudden onset of the epidemic has disrupted established plans.

According to a number of restaurant business operators, although the entire restaurant industry still showed growth trend in 2019, many restaurant businesses showed a significant decline in performance due to the economic downturn cycle, the combination of insufficient passenger flow, rising raw materials and other factors, especially some chain restaurant brands, life is more difficult.

Different from some catering enterprises mentioned rent, food backlogs and other cost-climbing problems, in Jia Guolong's view, the current problems facing Xibei mainly focus on more than 20,000 employees pay.

Affected by the epidemic, some places have postponed the Spring Festival holiday to February 10, but during this period, employees'wages still need to be paid according to the country's requirements. "We now have more than 10,000 people living in dormitories and almost 10,000 people going home. The family can not come, the dormitory can not go out, the latter has to manage good food, good housing, good management safety, in the staff did not carry out the work, the company does not have the operating income, when the resumption of work deposit unknown circumstances, the salary as usual to pay in full brings the pressure is really very big. " Jia Guolong has calculated an account to the "CAIJING" reporter, xibei has more than 20,000 employees, and the normal monthly salary expenditure is nearly 160 million yuan, or nearly 500 million yuan in three months.

Although the size of the staff is less than Xibei, but the founder of Banu Maodu Hot Pot du Zhongbing also have deep feelings. It told Caijing that with the year-end settlement of loans, payment of salaries and year-end bonuses, the cash flow of enterprises was tight. Many catering enterprises originally wanted to rely on the Lunar New Year consumption to "return blood, " but under the influence of the epidemic, not only did not have the operating income "the income" , also became the pure expense. If there is no cash flow in a month, only the cash flow of expenditure, most catering enterprises can hardly carry out a month. At worst, a minimum of six months of cash reserves is needed to protect against risk.

But for most restaurant companies, it is already difficult to survive for a month. "The wechat group, where I work, has been discussing cash flow issues day in and day out, and some are even considering using platforms such as Yelp and ele.me to apply for loans to tide them over, " said the head of a catering company, if the epidemic continues, the cash flow problem will be overwhelming many catering companies in 2020, "the last Straw. ".

Almost at the same time, in this sudden hit, the catering industry self-employed also face the "life and death" problem.

"It's expected to last until the beginning of the second lunar month, and if it doesn't start, there will definitely be layoffs, " one tea shop owner told his friends about the impact of the current outbreak on the shop.

According to the boss, the monthly salary of the Aunty employed in the shop is around 3000 yuan. If the work can not start at the beginning of February in the lunar calendar, some people can only be fired. And what does a 3,000 yuan income mean to these families? "They are generally the main source of income for families, so if they are laid off, their family life will be greatly affected. "

If the outbreak continues to worsen, I'm afraid the milk tea shop will have to close down. In"CAIJING"reporter recently interviewed more than self-employed, get into the same predicament as the owner of tea shop is not a minority.

Shut down and then shut down

Coincidentally, there are more industries and enterprises in the impact of the epidemic "suffering. ".

The director of a Wenzhou Construction Company who wanted to enjoy the Spring Festival holiday abroad was filled with anxiety and anxiety. Affected by the epidemic, if the company can not start construction before the end of January, he will face the project late default, high rental equipment costs.

The director of the construction company has dozens of projects, each of dozens or even hundreds of people, the total size of workers up to, people. According to its introduction, the enterprise is part of the long holiday industry, in previous years are generally in January 12 before the official start, but this year is not expected, can only wait for notification, all projects in a stagnant state.

In his view, even if he could return to work, there would be no point, because the workers could not return to Wenzhou. Under the latest local arrangement, which extends the holiday to February 10, only a few people are on duty even on that day. "In Wenzhou, factories are basically unable to resume work and the impact is very serious. "

According to the director, one of his concrete companies, Hubei accounted for 40 percent of the 150 drivers, "these people are definitely not coming back, the site must be closed. "

The loss to the company as a result of the suspension of the project is the delay in the construction period, the direct result of which is the payment of party a's overdue payment, in addition to the rental of a lot of equipment, even if it does not start, there are rental expenses, "The extension of the construction period can also be discussed with party a, but the leasing equipment has contracts, equipment leaseholder also has costs, it is more difficult to negotiate. "

According to the director of the introduction, although belong to the construction industry, but the company executives are paid leave. According to preliminary statistics, the cost of renting equipment for the company is one hundred thousand RMB a day, and the cost of salary is one million RMB a month.

The company's financial accounts were all at a standstill during the holiday. Although the construction company, which has annual revenue of one billion RMB, still has a certain amount of capital left, the loss caused by the project's stagnation is also a big blow.

The scale of the enterprise is still difficult, and some small and even micro-enterprises may be as difficult as piling beans on the tip of a needle.

The head of an e-commerce platform in Dongguan said in an interview with the CAIJING reporter that in recent years, with the competition on domestic e-commerce platforms heating up, the platform's internal policies have led to fewer business opportunities and excessively high advertising costs, this in turn led to a sharp drop in earnings, a dilemma that was reflected in the 2019 financial statements. In 2019, the company made a net profit of only 5 million yuan on sales of nearly 120 million yuan, according to the company.

"We have been out of production for almost a month and have no revenues, but we still have to spend a lot of money on labour, rent and so on. Even after the resumption of work, because our electronic products are supplied by the supply chain semi-finished products, suppliers are expected to resume normal delivery until March. So we need to wait until the middle or late March before we can have sufficient sales of goods,"said the person in charge, the Enterprise must bear the fund flow in the short term the pressure is not small. A smooth transition will require the recovery of January and February targets in March, but that will be difficult to achieve. If that does not happen, the first quarter is bound to be a big loss.

Some of the leaders of small and medium-sized enterprises admitted to the CAIJING reporter in an interview that this is a special stage and they definitely want to help the country do more, but they are actually the innocent group under the epidemic, who will protect the financial resources of the employees during the epidemic and protect the losses of the micro-enterprises during the epidemic? And if these pressures and losses are mishandled, the enterprise is likely to "collapse" , resulting in employee unemployment.

"It's Dead Tone now, especially this difficult year. If the epidemic is not effectively controlled, many small and medium-sized enterprises will go under in 2020, " said a company head in charge of rural electric vehicle production, at the end of last year, the state launched an air pollution warning, and the enterprise stopped production for two consecutive months. Expected to achieve efficiency growth in 2020, but the epidemic led to product delivery delays, customer cancellations, operating capital disruption, can be described as "even worse. ".

Financial Rescue at first

The impact of the epidemic, has spread from the strike on the industry, to more businesses, even individuals. This has also attracted the attention of the relevant regulatory authorities.

On February 1, five departments, including the People's Bank of China, the Ministry of Finance, the China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission, the Securities Regulatory Commission and the Foreign Exchange Bureau, jointly issued the notice on further strengthening financial support to prevent and control the spread of pneumonia in the COVID-19, pointing out that for the wholesale and retail, accommodation and catering, logistics and transportation, cultural tourism and other industries that have been greatly affected by the epidemic, as well as enterprises with prospects for development but are temporarily affected by the epidemic, in particular small and micro enterprises, enterprises seriously affected by the outbreak of the epidemic may extend or renew their loans if they have difficulty in repaying the loans due; and they may do so by lowering the interest rates on loans, increasing the amount of credit loans and medium-and long-term loans, we will support relevant enterprises in overcoming the impact of the epidemic and disasters.

Earlier, on January 26, the China Banking Regulatory Commission issued a notice on strengthening financial services in the banking and insurance industry, in coordination with the prevention and control of COVID-19 pneumonia, it also puts forward specific requirements for the financial services of distressed enterprises.

Then, including the Central Bank headquarters in Shanghai, the Central Bank's Business Management Department (Beijing) , the Central Bank's Chongqing Business Management Department, and the Central Bank's Guangzhou Branch announced the work arrangements on the epidemic prevention and control. As far as financial support is concerned, the multi-regional branches of the Central Bank encourage financial institutions to give preferential treatment in pricing and guarantee, implement special preferential interest rates and other support methods; in the examination and approval process, green channels for special credit examination and approval may be established, for enterprises involved in epidemic prevention and control, reasonable credit applications should be handled in special and urgent ways, with simplified procedures, quick examination and approval, and prompt issuance.

Under the epidemic situation, some banking institutions, including big state-owned banks, joint-stock banks, policy banks and city commercial banks, have taken corresponding relief measures for small and micro enterprises and individual industrial and commercial households. Such as the Agricultural Bank, the Construction Bank, the Bank of Communications, the CITIC Bank and others have issued relevant policies, during the prevention and control of the COVID-19 epidemic, for the prevention and control of the epidemic corresponding small and micro enterprises, individual businesses operating loans on the basis of the current interest rate cut by 0.5 percentage points and other measures.

At the same time, the Bank of China, the Postal Savings Bank, the China Merchants Bank, the micro-public Bank and others proposed that, in the light of the actual situation, for enterprises affected by the epidemic that are operating normally and have encountered temporary difficulties, support is provided by reducing or waiving overdue interest and by extending loans.

"CAIJING" reporters also noted that at present, the bank's credit support mainly around the epidemic started, the basic biopharmaceutical, medical devices, medical research and other fields customers. But even in those areas, banks have "turned down" companies applying for loans during the outbreak.

Romine, chairman of Hubei Changjiangyuan Pharmaceutical (hereinafter referred to as "Changjiangyuan Pharmaceutical") Co. , Ltd. , who is in the front line of the epidemic, was deeply impressed. After the outbreak, he began to large-scale procurement, deployment of medical supplies to the front line, which requires adequate financial support. But when he submitted a loan application to a bank he had long communicated with, he was "politely declined" .

According to public information, Changjiang source pharmaceutical is affiliated to Changjiang Pharmaceutical Group, which currently has an output value of more than 3 billion yuan and a market value of nearly 4 billion yuan.

While other industries have been hit by the epidemic, industries such as pharmaceuticals are seen as ushering in a new round of development. "We've been shut out of this situation, and it's going to be even harder for the unestablished players in other industries, " Romine said.

Feng Zhuohui, general manager of Golden Wave Star Nonwovens Co. , Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as "golden wave star") , who is not in the front line of the fight against the epidemic but has also worked overtime for many days because of the epidemic, talked about applying for loans from banks in recent years, the answer was three words: it's too hard. According to Feng Zhuohui, Jinlangxing Main non-woven processing, the outbreak is mainly the production of protective clothing.

It is understood that the company's products are mainly sold in foreign markets, but under the influence of factors such as sino-us trade frictions, only a modest profit of 500,000 yuan was realized when the turnover reached 50 million yuan in 2019, the company has shrunk from a few hundred at its peak in recent years to a few dozen today.

"In the course of the company's performance and personnel changes, if there is any risk, the bank will immediately take away the loan; if the business situation is even worse, there will be no loan at all, " Fung recalled.

But in this outbreak, compared to other enterprises, Yangtse Pharmaceutical and Jin Langxing is "lucky" . It is understood that the Hubei Branch and the Guangdong Branch of the Agricultural Development Bank of China reached out to the two enterprises, and quickly completed two loans (40 million yuan for Changjiang Yuan and 5 million yuan for Jinlangxing) .

It is worth noting that in addition to banks and other financial institutions taking relief measures targeting small and micro enterprises, including Wanda Business Management Group, Longhu Group, New City Holdings, Aegean Sea Group and other companies have announced for its mall tenants rent relief measures.

But to what extent can these measures alleviate the plight of msmes currently hit by the epidemic?

"usually, a bank loan has to take into account factors such as whether your cash flow is stable, whether you have collateral, etc. . Normally, we don't have enough credit lines, but if the epidemic continues, we may have to 'beg' The bank to provide funds, but according to the bank's approval process, it is difficult to 'put out the fire' in a timely manner. On the other hand, the real estate company's rent reduction seems to have helped us solve a big problem, but after being forced to suspend business, the wages of thousands of employees are still on us. "One senior executive at a large restaurant company said bluntly that at the moment, many of the affected companies do not have the credit to support them, and even measures such as deferring payments, waiving overdue interest and waiving rents, for some of the small and medium enterprises, that is, being able to carry the load again, can not solve the fundamental problem.

Regarding the current difficulties of enterprises and the effectiveness of related measures, Bu Zhenxing, a senior economist at the Postal Savings Bank, pointed out in an interview with the CAIJING reporter that from the perspective of enterprises, because of the outbreak of the disease, production was suspended, the so-called measures in the financial sector, such as renewing loans and lowering interest rates, are only to keep enterprises from notionally defaulting. However, the cost of enterprises is not only the cost of capital, but also the cost of rent and labor, etc. , after all, relying solely on financial support is limited. What enterprises need more are orders and entry items. Secondly, the differentiated and targeted credit policy, although it sounds very nice, still needs supporting technical and human support. There is no credit research, it is an objective fact that in the event of a default, credit officers still have to bear responsibility; moreover, banks are currently affected by the epidemic and are unable to carry out all their work and many policies are not fully implemented.

Looking for more support

"A drop in the bucket! " In response to the current measures, several executives from small and medium-sized enterprises who have been hit by the epidemic told CAIJING that if the epidemic continues and there are no effective policies to be introduced on a wider scale, many enterprises may not be able to see the warm sun after the haze.

At the moment, the inflection point has not been reached. As of 2400 hours on January 31,11,791 confirmed cases, 1795 severe cases, 259 deaths, 243 cured cases and 17,988 suspected cases have been reported nationwide.

On the other hand, the outbreak has attracted global attention. On January 30, the World Health Organization (WHO) officially declared the outbreak as a "public health emergency of international concern" (PHEIC) in Geneva. There is a view that, although this does not mean that China is classified as an "affected country, " as the epidemic develops, its negative impact on China's economy will cause market concerns, and industries such as tourism and foreign trade may be hit hard again, and is unlikely to recover anytime soon.

Many small and medium-sized micro-business owners who called for a wider range of "tax reduction and fee reduction" policy. "whether it is possible to set a minimum wage instead of paying it in full for employees who are unable to return to work normally after the outbreak, or whether tax and fees should be appropriately reduced or waived, the social security payment quota should be flexible, or whether the enterprises affected by the outbreak should be given a certain wage subsidy, or whether the minimum wage should be set for employees who are unable to work normally. " The head of the e-commerce platform said bluntly, in good times, share the fruits with employees, but in tough times, employees are expected to work with the company to overcome them, rather than leaving the company to carry the load.

Yam has also put forward a number of specific proposals in the "recommendations" , these include: Appropriate Reduction or exemption of value-added tax in sectors seriously affected by the epidemic in the first quarter, especially in the transportation (civil aviation, road passenger transport, water passenger transport and taxi) , tourism, catering, accommodation, etc. , in order to reduce income tax, the amount of loss can be deducted from the amount of profit month, and the rate of social insurance contribution can be further reduced by 1 and 2 percentage points, respectively, to reduce the burden on enterprises For a temporary period of one quarter, enterprises may be granted a financial discount on interest paid to industries that have been damaged during part of the period affected by the epidemic; enterprises and individuals participating in the donation may be given an income tax or individual income tax credit, not Subject to the current enterprise income tax pre-profit limit of 12% , encourage social donations, etc. .

Referring to the economic and financial sector's specific countermeasures, the Minsheng Banking Corp chief researcher wrote in Caijing that monetary policy should achieve "two reductions and three increases. ". "Two falls" means that according to the development of the epidemic situation and the needs of the economy, LPR will be guided to cut interest rates and implement standard reduction in a timely manner, while MLF, SLF and other monetary policy tools will be flexibly used to innovate special liquidity support tools for responding to the epidemic situation, finally, reduce the cost of financing for enterprises and residents.

"three improvements" , namely: speeding up the approval of applications for capital replenishment by financial institutions, and improving the ability of financial institutions to serve the real economy, especially private enterprises, micro-and small-scale enterprises, and enterprises in areas where the epidemic is serious; To strengthen the multi-party information connection among banks, governments and enterprises, and to suggest that supervisory departments coordinate with government departments in areas where the epidemic is serious, and to maximize the sharing of information involving enterprises in all aspects with relevant financial institutions, to improve the long-distance service ability and service efficiency of banks, if necessary, the local government shall determine the white list of key enterprises for epidemic prevention and control, and the local government shall give credit endorsement, and the financial institutions shall give innovative financial support such as low-interest credit loans; It is suggested that the regulatory authorities should speed up the identification and disposal of non-performing loans, promulgate industry-wide guidelines on loan due diligence and exemption as soon as possible, and increase the tolerance of the regulatory authorities to non-performing loans of financial institutions. In the context of epidemic prevention and control, financial institutions to lend, willing to lend, able to lend the environment.

And in the above mentioned Jia Guolong, Romine, Feng Zhuohui and other business leaders, the introduction of a wider range of effective policies is certainly the primary task at present, but how to put these policies into practice, still need more efforts.

"There are only two words: 'implementation' . Don't make empty promises, don't engage in formalism, don't make empty promises and cliches, and help the enterprise with practical actions. "With concerted efforts, we can bring new vitality to the survival and development of small and medium-sized enterprises and strengthen our determination to continue, " a private enterprise executive told CAIJING.

Of course, for those industries, businesses and individuals that have been hit by the new pneumonia epidemic, it would have been better if it had ended sooner. Wu Yu, a Chongqing bed-and-breakfast operator, and Lin Ke, head of a beijing-based travel agency, both posted a photo on a friend's circle that read: "No one in the world wants world peace and good weather more than we do. "

At the request of the interviewee, Wu Yu and Lin Ke were assumed names

(additional reporting by Caijing reporter Yu Yan and intern Zhang Linyi)
